abstract: Kelli Tennant, a former sports broadcaster and college athlete, filed a lawsuit alleging that he aggressively groped her in a hotel room. He denied the accusation.
snippet: Kelli Tennant, a former sports broadcaster and college athlete, filed a lawsuit alleging that he aggressively groped her in a hotel room. He denied the accusation.
lead_paragraph: Luke Walton, the N.B.A. coach who recently left the Los Angeles Lakers and was hired by the Sacramento Kings, has been sued by a former sports broadcaster who said he sexually assaulted her in a hotel room in 2014.

lead_paragraph: Marsala isn’t having a comeback. The fortified Sicilian wine hasn’t gone anywhere. It’s probably sitting in your pantry, where you left it, if you even left it there at all.

abstract: Moving into a home that belonged to your parents — where you lived as a teenager — can be challenging. Especially if it’s 100 years old.
snippet: Moving into a home that belonged to your parents — where you lived as a teenager — can be challenging. Especially if it’s 100 years old.
lead_paragraph: When Kim Hammond was a teenager in the late 1960s, his parents bought a proud stone house on a hill in Baltimore County, Md., and he immediately recognized it as remarkable.

abstract: A selection of recent poetry books (plus Whitman’s ruminations); and a peek at what our colleagues around the newsroom are reading.
snippet: A selection of recent poetry books (plus Whitman’s ruminations); and a peek at what our colleagues around the newsroom are reading.
lead_paragraph: WALT WHITMAN SPEAKS, edited by Brenda Wineapple. (Library of America, $19.95.) “I seem to be developing into a garrulous old man,” Whitman told the friend who transcribed these thoughts on topics from sex to democracy to his work (“I have been deliberate … but I have never looked for finish”).

abstract: Democrats court a new voting bloc: people who don’t own homes.
snippet: Democrats court a new voting bloc: people who don’t own homes.
lead_paragraph: Renters hold little sway in Washington. They vote at lower rates than homeowners. They’re generally represented in Congress by homeowners. They have no deep-pocketed lobbyists. And their problems, if anyone considers them at all, are typically waved off as problems for local government.

abstract: The Easter Egg Roll bore the hallmarks of holidays under President Trump, including not just the usual festivities but also exchanges about decapitation, impeachment and the wall.
snippet: The Easter Egg Roll bore the hallmarks of holidays under President Trump, including not just the usual festivities but also exchanges about decapitation, impeachment and the wall.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — At the White House Easter Egg Roll on Monday, President Trump ditched his escort — the Easter bunny — to take up a decidedly unfestive agenda: He fielded questions about impeachment and unruly advisers before briefing a child about the construction of a wall at the southwestern border.

abstract: In the On Politics newsletter: Democrats hoping to avoid Jeb Bush’s 2016 fate are finding themselves in familiar political minefields.
snippet: In the On Politics newsletter: Democrats hoping to avoid Jeb Bush’s 2016 fate are finding themselves in familiar political minefields.
lead_paragraph: Hi. Welcome to On Politics, your guide to the day in national politics. I’m Matt Flegenheimer, your temporary host. Lisa Lerer is on vacation, beach-reading Mueller report footnotes.
